abstract: >
  Version 2.4 extends the photometric-chromatic analysis of interstellar object 3I/ATLAS (C/2025 N1)
  with complete Minor Planet Center coverage through 2025-11-13 (4,413 observations). The analysis reveals
  a full activity cycle from pre-perihelion optical acceleration (peak: 2025-10-02) to post-perihelion
  deceleration, validated by independent morphological evidence from Nordic Optical Telescope imaging.
  The optical acceleration proxy demonstrates ~4-week early detection capability compared to orbital
  non-gravitational solutions. All datasets, scripts, and verification artefacts are cryptographically
  timestamped via OpenTimestamps (Bitcoin blockchain) and GPG-signed for complete reproducibility.
